result.execSummary:
The defendant Stephanie L. Holtz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fraud/Innkeeper,etc-Nonpayment (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.21(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent with: Waushara Co Case No. 2016CM000065

miscConds.notes: Restitution ordered as to both Waushara Co Case Nos. 2015CM000483 and 2016CM000065 in the total amount of $2339.91 ($504.21 as to 15CM-483 and $1835.70 as to 16CM-65) is ordered to be repaid at the rate of $100.00 per month, commencing no later than August 1, 2016.  A total monthly payment of $100.00 is ordered as to both cases.  Defendant is to receive a $90.00 credit for deposits paid directly to the Waushara Co Clerk of Court's office prior to sentencing.  Payment of $90.00 has been forwarded from the Waushara Co Clerk of Court's Office to the Department of Corrections for disbursement.

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant is prohibited from issuing any checks for payment.  Defendant may possess a debit card, however; is not to possess any credit cards.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
